Modifications and scope deviations from upstream
------------------------------------------------

scripts/wait-for-text.sh
    Vendored unmodified from upstream
    `skills/tmux/scripts/wait-for-text.sh` (main, fetched 2026-05-01).

skills/tmux/scripts/find-sessions.sh
    Not vendored. Most of its value is in cross-socket scanning under
    `CLAUDE_TMUX_SOCKET_DIR`, which doesn't apply here (this setup
    uses the default tmux server with everything visible to plain
    `tmux ls`).

SKILL.md
    Original to this repo. Upstream's SKILL.md is built around an
    isolated-socket pattern for driving REPLs and debuggers, which
    this setup explicitly does not adopt (sessions must stay visible
    to default `tmux ls`). The patterns retained here are the literal
    send-keys form, control-key notation, and capture-pane polling;
    the Claude-pane specifics (vim-mode submit, lost-leading-char
    workaround) are not in upstream.
